CONTENT: 1. **The Pre-Geometric Exclusions (Lemma [§3.2.2], Lemma [§3.2.3]):** The argument eliminates all graph candidates containing cyclic topologies or short-range loops, ensuring the initial state remains strictly pre-geometric and empty of pre-existing area.
