CONTENT: Any localized excitation characterized by a trivial topology, constituting an unbraided cluster with trivial Jones Polynomial $V_{\xi}(t) = 1$, is dynamically unstable and subject to immediate dissolution. The absence of non-trivial invariants ($w=0, L=0$) renders the cluster susceptible to the Catalytic Deletion Flux $J_{out}$ [(§5.2.7)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.2/#5.2.7), which is amplified by the density-dependent stress term $3\lambda_{cat}\rho^2$, driving the configuration toward the vacuum equilibrium.
