FILE: 02-players/06-fermions/6.2.md L565
CONTENT: **Substep 7.1: For $n=3$.** Tripartite braids possess non-trivial invariants ($w \neq 0$, possible $L \neq 0$); stability derives from primeness (irreducibility, no complexity-lowering paths without axiom violation; cross-ref. [(§6.4.1)](/monograph/players/fermions/6.4/#6.4.1)). The non-abelian $B_3$ generates $\mathfrak{su}(3)$. Minimality traces to Axiom 2 (3 as primitive). Cross-reference [(§3.5.1.1)](/monograph/rules/architecture/3.5/#3.5.1.1) positions primes as protected logical qubits, with infinite $\Delta F$ for global unbraiding per [(§2.7.2)](/monograph/rules/axioms/2.7/#2.7.2).
