FILE: 02-players/06-fermions/6.3.md L28
CONTENT: A crossing in a braid diagram corresponds to a specific, physical modification of the underlying causal graph. As established in the definition of the geometric quantum [(§2.3.2)](/monograph/rules/axioms/2.3/#2.3.2), a connection between two disparate points requires a mediating structure, specifically, the instantiation of a 3-cycle. Therefore, every crossing in the braid topology physically necessitates at least one new 3-cycle bridge in the graph.
