FILE: 02-players/06-fermions/6.3.md L39
CONTENT: The **Torsional Complexity**, denoted $C_T$, is defined strictly as a scalar quantity quadratically proportional to the Writhe $w(\beta)$ of the ribbon configuration. The value of $C_T$ is determined by the pathfinding penalties imposed by the Principle of Unique Causality [(§2.3.3)](/monograph/rules/axioms/2.3/#2.3.3), subject to the condition of **Quadratic Scaling**, wherein the complexity satisfies the relation $C_T = k_t \cdot w(\beta)^2$, with $k_t$ serving as a dimensionless scaling constant.
