FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.1.md L83
CONTENT: 2.  **Inductive Extension:** The construction extends inductively on the word length $k$. Assuming all words of length $k$ map surjectively, for length $k+1$, the appended generator $\sigma_j$ composes with the prior sequence $\Phi(w_k)$. This composition preserves the **Minimal Crossing Number** $C[\beta]$ [(§6.3.1)](/monograph/players/fermions/6.3/#6.3.1), ensuring no overcounting of isotopy classes.
