FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.1.md L84
CONTENT: 3.  **Local Commutativity:** The validity of the joint sequence follows from the locality of operations: disjoint supports for distant $\sigma_j$ commute without syndrome interference, while adjacent cases resolve via the Yang-Baxter relation [(§8.1.4)](/monograph/players/braids/8.1/#8.1.4), enforcing isotopic equivalence without creating redundant paths. Presentations of $B_n$ embed via such constructions (Jones, 1985: braids from projections), ensuring consistency with discrete graph methods.
