FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.1.md L88
CONTENT: 1.  **Topological Distinctness:** Distinct reduced words (where no $\sigma_i \sigma_i^{-1} = 1$) yield minimal diagrams distinct up to isotopy (PUC prevents reducible Type II moves). The **Jones Polynomial** $V_\xi(t)$ [(§6.1.1)](/monograph/players/fermions/6.1/#6.1.1) serves as the faithful invariant; since $\mathcal{R}$ sequences preserve the **Writhe** $w(\beta)$ and **Linking Matrix** $L_{ij}$ [(§6.1.1)](/monograph/players/fermions/6.1/#6.1.1), distinct words map to graphs with distinct polynomial invariants.
