CONTENT: 1.  **Metric Separation:** If $|i-j| \ge 2$, the pair $(i, i+1)$ is disjoint from $(j, j+1)$. The subgraphs are spatially separated by an **Undirected Metric Distance** $\bar{d}(u,v) > 2$ [(§3.5.4.2)](/monograph/rules/architecture/3.5/#3.5.4.2). This separation ensures no shared vertices or edges beyond the unstrained part, preventing overlapping **2-path motifs** that could couple the operations.
