FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.6.md L123
CONTENT: The **mass prediction lemma** [(§8.6.3)](/monograph/players/braids/8.6/#8.6.3) validates the entire chain of logic by comparing the predicted W and Z boson masses to experiment. The derivation uses *no free parameters* tuned to these masses; it uses only the vacuum density $\rho^*$ (derived from friction) and the geometric constants ($\alpha_{topo}, M$). This parameter-free prediction is the hallmark of a constrained geometric theory, distinct from the effective field theory approach where masses are renormalized inputs. The agreement suggests that the vacuum density operates as a fundamental constant of nature, akin to the role of the cosmological constant in the thermodynamic derivation of Einstein's equations by **[(Jacobson, 1995)](/monograph/appendices/a-references#A.34)**, setting the scale for all inertial phenomena.
