--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.6.md L141
CONTENT: Extensive entropy $S = c N$ [(§5.1.2)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.1/#5.1.2) dictates that the collective condensate strength is an intensive property, independent of the global volume $N$. It satisfies $\langle \phi \rangle^2 \propto \rho_3^* N_\xi$, where $N_\xi$ is the number of available 3-cycles within the correlation volume $V_\xi$. The correlation length scales as $\xi^{-1} = \sqrt{\rho_3^*}$ from the decay $e^{-d/\xi}$ [(§5.5.5)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.5/#5.5.5). The dimensionful anchor $\kappa_m \approx 0.170$ MeV per 3-cycle [(§7.4.2)](/monograph/players/topology/7.4/#7.4.2) relates the braid free energy to quanta count via $F_{\mathrm{braid}} = \kappa_m N_3$ [(§7.4.3)](/monograph/players/topology/7.4/#7.4.3).
