FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.6.md L144
CONTENT: The volume $V_\xi$ satisfies Ahlfors regularity $c_1 r^4 \leq |B(r)| \leq c_2 r^4$ [(§5.5.7)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.5/#5.5.7), with curvature bounds $|K(u,v)| \leq 2$ [(§5.5.4)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.5/#5.5.4). Central limit theorem damping over independent subregions yields a stable intensive variance $\mathrm{Var}(\rho_3^*) \sim 1/N_\xi$, where $N_\xi = \frac{V_\xi}{\mathrm{vol}(\gamma)} \sim \rho_3^{*-3}$.
