FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.6.md L147
CONTENT: The effective VEV constitutes $v = \sqrt{2 \kappa_m \rho_3^* N_\xi}$. Because $N_\xi$ depends only on the local correlation length and the equilibrium density $\rho_3^* \approx 0.029$ [(§5.3.4)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.3/#5.3.4), the resulting VEV is strictly intensive. Calibrating the fundamental topological anchor $\kappa_m$ against the aggregate count $N_\xi$ in the 4-dimensional correlation volume yields the observed macroscopic energy scale of $246$ GeV.
