FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.6.md L150
CONTENT: The Ahlfors-David regularity theorem guarantees that the causal metric, emergent from rewrite distances $d(u,v) = \inf \{\text{length}(\gamma) \mid \gamma \text{ path } u \to v\}$ [(§5.5.2)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.5/#5.5.2), supports 4-dimensional volume growth. The Reifenberg theorem for local regularity implies manifold smoothness [(§5.5.1)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.5/#5.5.1). The $\epsilon$-Hausdorff distance $\epsilon \sim \rho_3^*$ ensures the graph approximates $\mathbb{R}^4$ balls up to scale $\xi$. By relying on the intensive capacity $N_\xi$, the vacuum preserves the VEV as a cosmological constant, preventing mass evaporation as the global $N$ expands over time.
