FILE: 02-players/08-braids/8.6.md L161
CONTENT: Crucially, this defines the Higgs VEV as an *intensive* property of the vacuum, decoupled from the total size of the universe $N$. If the VEV depended inversely on $N$, the mass of all elementary particles would decay as the universe expanded—a catastrophic instability that would dissolve atoms over cosmic time. Instead, because the causal graph's interactions are shielded by exponential correlation decay [(§5.1.3)](/monograph/rules/equilibrium/5.1/#5.1.3), a particle only "feels" the geometric drag of the 3-cycles within its immediate causal horizon.
