CONTENT: The **decay tunneling lemma** [(§9.3.4)](/monograph/players/unification/9.3/#9.3.4) resolves the paradox of why higher-generation particles (like muons and taus) are stable enough to be detected but unstable enough to decay. If they are protected by topology, why do they decay at all? The answer lies in the stochastic nature of the vacuum. While local moves cannot "untie" the knot of a muon to turn it into an electron, the probabilistic nature of the vacuum, the "rewrite bath", allows for rare, non-local fluctuations that can bridge the topological gap.
