CONTENT: While geometric stabilizers check the "empty space" between ribbons (the cycles), ribbon stabilizers check the ribbons themselves. The **ribbon commutation proof** [(§10.2.5)](/monograph/players/computation/10.2/#10.2.5) ensures that verifying the integrity of a ribbon segment, making sure it isn't broken or twisted internally, does not interfere with the other checks. Again, the "rule of two" (even overlap) guarantees that these distinct types of measurements can coexist peacefully, allowing the system to monitor the wire's continuity without disrupting the signal flowing through it.
