FILE: 02-players/10-computation/10.2.md L291
CONTENT: Vertex stabilizers enforce a "flow conservation" law (akin to Kirchhoff's laws) at each node of the graph using $X$ operators. The **vertex commutation lemma** [(§10.2.7)](/monograph/players/computation/10.2/#10.2.7) confirms that checking the flow at node A doesn't mess up the flow check at node B, even if they are connected. Because both checks use the same type of operator ($X$) on the connecting line, they don't interfere with each other. This ensures that the conservation of "causal flux" can be monitored globally across the entire network without conflict.
